    "summary": "Reinout Polders is a Business Economist from the Erasmus University Rotterdam with a Master's Degree in Urban, Port and Transport Economics. He also holds a Master's Degree in Geographical Economics, obtained at the University of Utrecht. Mr. Polders has also passed level I and II of the CFA Program.\n\nMr. Polders joined MTBS early 2012, directly after his graduation. At MTBS, he has developed expertise in the fields of Port Economics, Financial Modelling, Traffic Forecasting, Project Finance Advisory, Economic Cost Benefit Analysis, Public-Private Partnerships and Transaction Advisory,\n\nMTBS is an international firm based in Rotterdam, specialized in Strategic and Financial Advisory Services focused on the Port and Transport Sector. Mr. Polders has conducted Projects for MTBS in the following countries: Canada, South Africa, the UK, the Netherlands, Belgium, Turkey, Slovenia, Ireland, the Kingdom of Saudi Arabia, Georgia, Egypt, Oman, Somaliland, Kenya, Tanzania and Nigeria. Mr. Polders is also involved as a lecturer for MTBS' Port Finance Courses that are organized together with Port Finance International. ",
